The paper deals with video processing and analysis, specifically in the context of first-person videos. This suggests that it could fall under several sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on visual data and the use of techniques such as frame selection and smoothing, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The use of multimodal data and annotations could also suggest a potential fit with cs.MM and cs.HC.
